                    <h3>Whiteboarding, Sketching and Getting Feedback</h3>
                    <p>Once I understand the design challenge and have researched the problem space, ideas will have started to mature about how we could do things better. I start on whiteboards and paper, fleshing out the quick wins and opportunities to elevate from my previous steps. I keep early designs loose and flexible, working big to small and answering one question at a time.</p>

                    <p>
                        Socializing these ideas early and often helps get buy-in and insight into what's easy, hard, and
                        unknown. Sharing at this stage, especially with engineering, lets us start considering what's MVP, next sprint and further down the road.</p>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

</section>

